  "body": "The `hack/local-up-cluster.sh` script doesn't support a user-value for the Kube-apiserver `--bind-address` option.\n\nThis is the IPs on which the Kube API will listen for secure API requests. The local-cluster-up script is set in such a way that it will only bind to the same IP as the one defined in `API_HOST_IP`:\n\n```\nAPI_HOST=${API_HOST:-127.0.0.1}\nAPI_HOST_IP=${API_HOST_IP:-${API_HOST}}\nAPI_BIND_ADDR=${API_HOST_IP:-\"0.0.0.0\"}\n```\n\nThe default value of `0.0.0.0` will never be used as `API_HOST_IP` is always set on the line before. \n\nThis means that today getting to the secure Kube API through the kube service IP doesn't work. (By default the secure API only binds to `127.0.0.1` on the host).\n\nProposal is to have a default of `0.0.0.0` for secure API binding, or whatever value is provided by the user.\n",
